# Apr-20 F/u 47: package-lock.json NOW committed for deterministic installs
# (see also .github/workflows/deploy.yml preflight which now uses `npm ci`).
# Prior state (gitignored) made CI installs non-deterministic — different
# runs could resolve different transitive deps. Committing the lockfile
# snapshots the current dep graph; updates via `npm install <pkg>` continue
# to regenerate it, just now the regenerations get committed + reviewed.

